@joshuamdavis: The issue is more like the height offset of the camera, not the zoom (the current function of the scroll wheel). The issue is that when someone stands in front of your avatar trying to talk to you (or shake hands due to how connections work), it becomes impossible to see them in the current camera's position. While the handshake system is something I don't think can ever be solved easily, the best case of something allowing the camera angle to actually show who is in front of a user, assuming the other person is the same height (smaller avatars are naturally just not going to work).

The best I can compare to is Second Life's camera, which actually had the focus point more on the top of the head but with some additional height so it was pointed partly downward (if I had to guess, I'm thinking the look at point was at Hifi's equal of Head_TopEnd), allowing me to always see when someone was in front. Just having the camera higher up pretty makes this possible.

EDIT: In other words, don't touch the scroll wheel: that's working fine as is. This is more of a camera setting to have a positional offset from where it should be.

